1
00:00:00,107 --> 00:00:07,492
(Beauty and Mr. Romantic)

2
00:00:13,408 --> 00:00:14,448
Do Ra!

3
00:00:15,948 --> 00:00:17,377
Are you all right?

4
00:00:17,647 --> 00:00:19,778
What's going on? Is something up?

5
00:00:20,078 --> 00:00:21,348
- It's nothing.
- It's nothing.

6
00:00:22,047 --> 00:00:24,187
Why did you choose
a cold day to film?

7
00:00:24,187 --> 00:00:25,487
Do something about this weather.

8
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:29,057
Hey, I'm fine. Get going.

9
00:00:29,057 --> 00:00:31,557
- I'll talk to him and catch up.
- Sure.

10
00:00:31,557 --> 00:00:32,958
- I'll get going.
- I'm fine.

11
00:00:39,638 --> 00:00:42,567
Unbelievable. This darn twig...

12
00:00:42,908 --> 00:00:44,438
almost had me crossing
to the underworld.

13
00:00:45,338 --> 00:00:47,847
It's dangerous to run in the woods.

14
00:00:47,847 --> 00:00:49,877
Why do you think they say
we should be humble...

15
00:00:50,078 --> 00:00:51,118
when we're out in the woods?

16
00:00:53,618 --> 00:00:54,648
Right.

17
00:00:55,948 --> 00:00:57,817
Anyway, thanks.

18
00:00:58,987 --> 00:01:01,788
You saved me yet again.

19
00:01:03,427 --> 00:01:06,527
What was it you wanted to ask
for you to run like that?

20
00:01:06,698 --> 00:01:08,868
Oh, that. Right.

21
00:01:09,497 --> 00:01:11,637
Your family name is Ko.

22
00:01:11,898 --> 00:01:13,538
You're Assistant Director
Ko Pil Seung.

23
00:01:14,038 --> 00:01:16,607
Do you have a relative
called Ko Dae Chung?

24
00:01:22,448 --> 00:01:23,478
What?

25
00:01:25,978 --> 00:01:28,788
"Ko Dae Chung?" Why?

26
00:01:28,848 --> 00:01:32,318
Ko Dae Chung was a guy I knew
when I was a kid.

27
00:01:32,788 --> 00:01:35,887
For some strange reason,
I think of him when I see you.

28
00:01:36,527 --> 00:01:39,758
You have the same surname,
and you both have curly hair.

29
00:01:40,258 --> 00:01:41,898
So I wondered if you were related.

30
00:01:46,137 --> 00:01:49,907
No relative of mine has that name.

31
00:01:52,178 --> 00:01:55,747
What kind of a name is Ko Dae Chung?
That's hilarious.

32
00:01:55,907 --> 00:01:57,878
Was he named that
so he'd take life easy?

33
00:02:01,988 --> 00:02:05,088
Sorry. I've never,
not even once, met anyone...

34
00:02:05,088 --> 00:02:06,618
with that name.

35
00:02:09,887 --> 00:02:10,887
I guess,

36
00:02:11,228 --> 00:02:13,758
having the same surname
doesn't mean everyone is related.

37
00:02:14,628 --> 00:02:17,667
That's right.
There are so many Kos out there.

38
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:20,667
So,

39
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:23,468
I guess that guy was
that memorable...

40
00:02:23,737 --> 00:02:25,008
if you keep thinking of him.

41
00:02:28,207 --> 00:02:31,278
The truth is, he followed me around
saying he had a crush on me.

42
00:02:33,077 --> 00:02:34,147
What?

43
00:02:34,448 --> 00:02:36,147
I'm his first love.

44
00:02:36,517 --> 00:02:39,818
In school, he insisted on giving me
a ride on his bike...

45
00:02:39,818 --> 00:02:41,887
and followed me around
to buy me tteokbokki.

46
00:02:43,357 --> 00:02:45,857
Anyway, that's what he did.

47
00:02:47,128 --> 00:02:50,198
Right. I see.

48
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:54,607
From now on,
don't think of him when you see me.

49
00:02:54,607 --> 00:02:55,867
I don't know him at all.

50
00:02:56,568 --> 00:02:57,867
And walk slowly.

51
00:02:58,038 --> 00:03:00,038
I have to set things up
for the shoot.

52
00:03:04,848 --> 00:03:05,848
Right.

53
00:03:06,278 --> 00:03:08,448
Dae Chung won't have relatives
that look like him.

54
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:11,147
He wasn't Ms. Kim's biological son.

55
00:03:16,288 --> 00:03:18,327
But why am I
reminded of Dae Chung...

56
00:03:18,628 --> 00:03:20,897
whenever I see
the Curly-haired Assistant Director?

57
00:03:21,728 --> 00:03:23,098
I don't get it.

58
00:03:26,598 --> 00:03:28,408
Do I miss him?

59
00:03:31,538 --> 00:03:32,837
No way.

60
00:03:33,878 --> 00:03:35,448
I'm losing my mind.

61
00:03:35,948 --> 00:03:37,478
That's just stupid.

62
00:03:38,517 --> 00:03:40,917
My heart almost dropped.

63
00:03:42,748 --> 00:03:43,848
Did Park Do Ra...

64
00:03:44,417 --> 00:03:46,658
ask me that knowing I was Dae Chung?

65
00:03:47,617 --> 00:03:49,327
No, it didn't seem like it.

66
00:03:50,457 --> 00:03:52,397
It's the darned curly hair.

67
00:03:52,758 --> 00:03:53,897
Should I get it straightened?

68
00:03:54,698 --> 00:03:56,767
No. She might suspect something.

69
00:03:58,137 --> 00:04:00,397
I said it wasn't me.
She'll take my word for it.

70
00:04:03,737 --> 00:04:04,808
Wait.

71
00:04:05,607 --> 00:04:07,508
When did I follow her around?

72
00:04:08,348 --> 00:04:10,107
She had a crush on me,
and she followed me around.

73
00:04:11,448 --> 00:04:12,878
This is unbelievable.

74
00:04:13,818 --> 00:04:16,848
When the stuntwoman comes this way,
you go up that way.

75
00:04:17,188 --> 00:04:19,517
Do Ra,
check the stuntwoman's last pose.

76
00:04:19,517 --> 00:04:21,728
- Okay.
- That will be your starting pose.

77
00:04:21,728 --> 00:04:22,857
- I'll check.
- Okay.

78
00:04:23,327 --> 00:04:25,258
Director, I have bad news.

79
00:04:25,657 --> 00:04:27,558
The stuntwoman
was in a fender-bender.

80
00:04:28,128 --> 00:04:29,168
What?

81
00:04:29,568 --> 00:04:31,438
It wasn't a serious accident,

82
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:33,868
but she fractured a rib or something
and couldn't move.

83
00:04:33,868 --> 00:04:35,668
She called to say she was on her way
to the hospital and couldn't come.

84
00:04:37,767 --> 00:04:39,837
We're already way behind schedule.

85
00:04:40,407 --> 00:04:41,647
This is terrible.

86
00:04:42,108 --> 00:04:44,977
Director. I'll do it myself.

87
00:04:45,418 --> 00:04:46,448
You can't.

88
00:04:52,558 --> 00:04:53,587
I mean...

89
00:04:53,717 --> 00:04:56,157
It's too dangerous
for her to do it herself.

90
00:04:56,657 --> 00:04:58,157
Yes, it is.

91
00:04:58,628 --> 00:05:01,698
We can't ask an actress
to roll down a dirty slope.

92
00:05:01,698 --> 00:05:03,467
It will be worse if you get hurt too.

93
00:05:03,727 --> 00:05:05,837
We'll look for another solution.

94
00:05:05,938 --> 00:05:08,207
Don't you worry, Ms. Park.
Take a break.

95
00:05:08,738 --> 00:05:09,767
Another solution?

96
00:05:10,008 --> 00:05:12,308
If we don't have a stuntwoman,
one of us can do it.

97
00:05:16,048 --> 00:05:17,048
Me?

98
00:05:18,178 --> 00:05:19,318
You want me to do it?

99
00:05:19,418 --> 00:05:21,147
You have boot camp experience.

100
00:05:21,448 --> 00:05:22,517
Who else can do it?

101
00:05:25,157 --> 00:05:26,188
Right.

102
00:05:26,758 --> 00:05:29,287
Of course, it should be me.
I'll do it.

103
00:05:30,827 --> 00:05:32,157
Are you serious?

104
00:05:32,157 --> 00:05:34,227
Wardrobe Team!
Do you have extra clothes?

105
00:05:45,608 --> 00:05:46,837
- What the heck?
- Let's see.

106
00:05:48,077 --> 00:05:49,477
You look pretty good.

107
00:05:49,748 --> 00:05:51,948
- Great. Let's do it.
- Wait.

108
00:05:52,678 --> 00:05:53,717
Mr. Ko.

109
00:05:54,277 --> 00:05:55,587
Maybe I should just do it.

110
00:05:55,587 --> 00:05:56,918
No, it's fine.

111
00:05:58,048 --> 00:05:59,387
I'll do it.

112
00:06:00,758 --> 00:06:02,258
Do your best, Pil Seung.

113
00:06:02,628 --> 00:06:03,657
Action!

114
00:06:06,957 --> 00:06:08,827
Cut! We can't use it.

115
00:06:09,168 --> 00:06:10,298
Pil Seung!

116
00:06:10,597 --> 00:06:13,438
It might feel weird,
but run more femininely.

117
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,568
Try it again!

118
00:06:26,217 --> 00:06:27,748
Cut! No way.

119
00:06:28,847 --> 00:06:30,748
Do something about the wig.

120
00:06:34,157 --> 00:06:35,558
Oh, no.

121
00:06:35,758 --> 00:06:37,087
Cameras rolling and action!

122
00:06:37,988 --> 00:06:39,498
Cut! Not good enough.

123
00:06:39,827 --> 00:06:41,897
Hey, wait for my cue!

124
00:06:41,897 --> 00:06:44,168
Cut! You rolled four times!

125
00:06:44,767 --> 00:06:45,798
Five times!

126
00:06:46,767 --> 00:06:47,798
Five times!

127
00:06:50,738 --> 00:06:52,678
Hye Soo!

128
00:06:52,837 --> 00:06:54,537
Cut. No good.

129
00:06:54,878 --> 00:06:56,878
We saw too much of your face.

130
00:07:01,787 --> 00:07:02,818
Hye Soo!

131
00:07:03,618 --> 00:07:04,748
- Hye Soo.
- No good!

132
00:07:05,787 --> 00:07:06,787
Pil Seung.

133
00:07:07,118 --> 00:07:08,887
Roll five times!

134
00:07:09,327 --> 00:07:11,287
- It seems just fine.
- Cameras, action!

135
00:07:16,967 --> 00:07:18,798
Hye Soo!

136
00:07:18,798 --> 00:07:20,568
- Cut, okay! That's it!
- My gosh.

137
00:07:21,808 --> 00:07:22,907
Get my jacket!

138
00:07:24,207 --> 00:07:25,238
Darn it.

139
00:07:28,137 --> 00:07:29,707
This is killing me.

140
00:07:29,707 --> 00:07:30,847
Good job.

141
00:07:31,448 --> 00:07:32,448
Next scene!

142
00:07:39,118 --> 00:07:40,957
Your legs.

143
00:07:49,397 --> 00:07:50,397
My gosh.

144
00:07:50,527 --> 00:07:52,668
You can't run away again.

145
00:07:52,668 --> 00:07:54,168
Will you let go of me?

146
00:07:54,198 --> 00:07:55,308
No way.

147
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:58,537
So you can run off like you did
at the department store?

148
00:07:59,137 --> 00:08:01,977
You must know
you did something dreadfully wrong.

149
00:08:01,977 --> 00:08:03,707
What did I do wrong? I never ran off.

150
00:08:03,948 --> 00:08:05,448
Why are you doing this to me?

151
00:08:05,448 --> 00:08:08,077
Forget the excuses.
Hand over the money.

152
00:08:08,618 --> 00:08:11,618
The money you took from Mr. Kim
by seducing him.

153
00:08:12,058 --> 00:08:14,418
Hand it over with interest
for the past 15 years.

154
00:08:14,887 --> 00:08:17,827
Are you out of your mind?
Who seduced whom?

155
00:08:17,858 --> 00:08:19,928
How dare you say such a thing?

156
00:08:20,058 --> 00:08:22,897
I hear your daughter is
very popular now.

157
00:08:22,897 --> 00:08:24,938
She's in TV dramas and commercials.

158
00:08:24,938 --> 00:08:27,438
She's raking in
all the money there is.

159
00:08:27,837 --> 00:08:29,467
And yet you never paid us back.

160
00:08:29,808 --> 00:08:31,207
How could you?

161
00:08:31,977 --> 00:08:35,508
So, 30,000 dollars in those days
is about 50,000 dollars now.

162
00:08:35,508 --> 00:08:38,878
If we count the interest,
you owe us over 100,000 dollars.

163
00:08:39,717 --> 00:08:41,888
What? 100,000 dollars?

164
00:08:43,148 --> 00:08:46,457
Lady. Do you think that much money
just falls out of the sky?

165
00:08:46,987 --> 00:08:49,087
And the money Mr. Kim gave me then,

166
00:08:49,087 --> 00:08:51,388
he gave it to me
with no strings attached.

167
00:08:51,388 --> 00:08:52,727
It was a gift.

168
00:08:52,997 --> 00:08:56,327
Are you the old man's wife
or something?

169
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:58,898
Who are you to demand I pay you back?

170
00:08:59,737 --> 00:09:02,668
From now on,
don't come looking for me again.

171
00:09:02,668 --> 00:09:05,877
If you do, I'll take action, okay?

172
00:09:06,207 --> 00:09:07,308
Fine!

173
00:09:07,707 --> 00:09:09,247
I'll just go
to the broadcasting station, then.

174
00:09:09,847 --> 00:09:13,577
I'll tell everyone Park Do Ra's mom
took our money and ran.

175
00:09:14,617 --> 00:09:15,747
What?

176
00:09:15,747 --> 00:09:18,658
That Park Do Ra's mom
seduced my daughter-in-law's dad...

177
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:20,087
and took his money.

178
00:09:20,117 --> 00:09:22,757
Because of Park Do Ra's mom,
the poor old man died.

179
00:09:22,757 --> 00:09:25,428
I'll go and tell everyone!

180
00:09:25,428 --> 00:09:27,627
My gosh. You mad woman.

181
00:09:27,627 --> 00:09:30,727
What the heck? You're insane.

182
00:09:35,007 --> 00:09:36,038
Goodness.

183
00:09:37,007 --> 00:09:38,007
Oh, gosh.

184
00:09:42,678 --> 00:09:44,408
- Hyun Chul.
- Mom. I'm heading out.

185
00:09:44,408 --> 00:09:46,148
- Where are you going?
- What?

186
00:09:46,347 --> 00:09:50,487
You don't go out on a motorcycle...

187
00:09:50,487 --> 00:09:52,288
to deliver stuff, do you?

188
00:09:52,757 --> 00:09:54,918
Don't do that, okay?

189
00:09:55,127 --> 00:09:58,928
If you go out on a motorcycle,
which is so dangerous,

190
00:09:58,928 --> 00:10:00,827
I really can't stand it.

191
00:10:00,827 --> 00:10:02,898
I'd rather starve
than make you do that.

192
00:10:03,127 --> 00:10:05,768
Okay. I'm just meeting someone
in the neighborhood.

193
00:10:05,967 --> 00:10:07,398
- See you.
- Hyun Chul.

194
00:10:07,398 --> 00:10:08,438
What?

195
00:10:09,107 --> 00:10:10,308
Be patient.

196
00:10:11,007 --> 00:10:14,207
I'll get you some money
to start the business.

197
00:10:14,877 --> 00:10:16,347
Maybe not 200,000 dollars,

198
00:10:16,377 --> 00:10:19,077
but I'm sure I can
get 100,000 dollars somehow.

199
00:10:20,678 --> 00:10:21,688
You, get 100,000 dollars?

200
00:10:22,448 --> 00:10:23,847
How would you do that?

201
00:10:24,648 --> 00:10:26,888
- See you later.
- Come on.

202
00:10:27,558 --> 00:10:30,428
Just you wait.
I'll get you the money.

203
00:10:30,658 --> 00:10:34,857
So don't feel intimidated
or shy, okay?

204
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:37,367
Okay, sure. I won't.

205
00:10:37,867 --> 00:10:38,898
A hundred grand?

206
00:10:39,298 --> 00:10:40,438
See you later.

207
00:10:48,808 --> 00:10:51,107
When the geotjeori's done,
make some green onion kimchi too.

208
00:10:51,607 --> 00:10:53,318
We sold out already.

209
00:10:53,918 --> 00:10:56,347
Already? Okay.

210
00:10:56,987 --> 00:10:59,558
Everyone's talking about
how great your kimchi is.

211
00:11:00,318 --> 00:11:01,757
I'm glad to hear that.

212
00:11:03,528 --> 00:11:05,757
Ms. Jang, Mr. Kang is here.

213
00:11:06,798 --> 00:11:08,928
I was going to drive myself.

214
00:11:09,898 --> 00:11:11,867
- Okay. I'll see you later.
- Yes.

215
00:11:11,867 --> 00:11:12,898
Oh, right.

216
00:11:13,467 --> 00:11:15,237
Does the soy sauce
marinated crab taste good?

217
00:11:15,367 --> 00:11:16,367
Yes.

218
00:11:16,367 --> 00:11:18,607
It's perfectly seasoned.
They will love it.

219
00:11:18,607 --> 00:11:19,638
Please don't worry.

220
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:22,377
Are you going to the airport now?

221
00:11:23,107 --> 00:11:24,278
I'm coming with you.

222
00:11:25,577 --> 00:11:27,617
I don't mind going alone.

223
00:11:27,617 --> 00:11:29,648
You don't have to come.

224
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:31,688
I'm not
in Auntie's good books already.

225
00:11:31,717 --> 00:11:33,857
Not going to the airport
will only make it worse.

226
00:11:34,617 --> 00:11:36,058
You must be happy...

227
00:11:36,058 --> 00:11:38,158
that you put yourself
in her good books.

228
00:11:56,178 --> 00:11:57,178
Honey.

229
00:11:58,077 --> 00:11:59,477
Isn't Auntie out yet?

230
00:12:00,717 --> 00:12:02,617
Why are you here?
You have a meeting to attend.

231
00:12:02,888 --> 00:12:03,888
I canceled it.

232
00:12:03,888 --> 00:12:06,018
Auntie is coming to visit
after a long time,

233
00:12:06,018 --> 00:12:07,818
so I can't concentrate on my work.

234
00:12:08,257 --> 00:12:09,388
Look at you.

235
00:12:10,158 --> 00:12:11,798
Are you happy that she's coming?

236
00:12:12,028 --> 00:12:14,398
You look like a little kid
waiting for his mom.

237
00:12:15,327 --> 00:12:16,327
Do I?

238
00:12:18,298 --> 00:12:19,367
There she is.

239
00:12:20,467 --> 00:12:21,467
Auntie.

240
00:12:21,837 --> 00:12:24,367
Hey, Jin Taek.

241
00:12:25,707 --> 00:12:26,737
My gosh.

242
00:12:26,737 --> 00:12:28,377
You must be exhausted
after a long flight.

243
00:12:28,377 --> 00:12:29,877
It wasn't so bad.

244
00:12:29,877 --> 00:12:32,877
And now that I see you,
I'm feeling a lot better.

245
00:12:32,948 --> 00:12:33,948
You are?

246
00:12:33,948 --> 00:12:37,717
Look at you, Jin Taek.
You haven't changed at all.

247
00:12:37,717 --> 00:12:39,658
And you haven't changed either.

248
00:12:39,658 --> 00:12:41,518
Actually, you've got younger
since I saw you last.

249
00:12:41,658 --> 00:12:43,587
I know you're lying.

250
00:12:44,087 --> 00:12:45,658
I'm serious, Auntie.

251
00:12:45,727 --> 00:12:48,257
To me, you always look the same.

252
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:51,227
Thank you for saying that.

253
00:12:51,668 --> 00:12:52,737
Auntie.

254
00:12:52,798 --> 00:12:54,737
Thank you for coming
all the way here.

255
00:12:54,737 --> 00:12:58,237
Hey, Soo Yeon.
I didn't know you were here.

256
00:12:58,237 --> 00:12:59,308
Have you been doing well?

257
00:12:59,308 --> 00:13:00,607
Yes, Auntie.

258
00:13:01,237 --> 00:13:03,077
I'm so glad that you look well.

259
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:04,948
Hello.

260
00:13:05,418 --> 00:13:08,048
Hey, Ae Kyo. You're here too.

261
00:13:08,688 --> 00:13:11,747
Why did you all come here
when you were so busy?

262
00:13:11,747 --> 00:13:15,058
I had to come to meet you
no matter how busy I was.

263
00:13:15,227 --> 00:13:16,587
- Thank you...
- Let's go, Auntie.

264
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:18,757
Okay. Let's go, Jin Taek.

265
00:13:18,757 --> 00:13:20,698
- Come here, Soo Yeon.
- Okay.

266
00:13:25,597 --> 00:13:27,398
- It's so good to see you.
- All right.

267
00:13:27,898 --> 00:13:29,607
They look so happy without me.

268
00:13:30,808 --> 00:13:33,507
I understand
how Auntie and Chairman Gong are feeling.

269
00:13:34,308 --> 00:13:36,247
But how could that brat Soo Yeon
be doing this to me?

270
00:13:37,607 --> 00:13:40,418
Would it kill her to turn around
and tell me to join them?

271
00:13:41,247 --> 00:13:42,388
That darn brat.

272
00:13:43,117 --> 00:13:45,717
They are treating me
like a third wheel.

273
00:13:50,028 --> 00:13:52,028
- Do you like the soup?
- Yes, it's refreshing.

274
00:13:52,357 --> 00:13:54,127
You're back after a long time.

275
00:13:54,127 --> 00:13:56,398
Just make yourself at home
and stay as long as you like.

276
00:13:56,398 --> 00:13:58,168
You should meet your friends too.

277
00:13:58,668 --> 00:14:01,097
Okay. That's my plan.

278
00:14:01,097 --> 00:14:02,808
I have some business to take care of.

279
00:14:02,808 --> 00:14:05,337
I'll stay long
spending a lot of time with you.

280
00:14:05,337 --> 00:14:06,638
Do you really mean that?

281
00:14:07,207 --> 00:14:09,448
I don't want you to leave soon
just like you did the last time.

282
00:14:09,448 --> 00:14:10,847
You promised me.

283
00:14:11,048 --> 00:14:12,877
Okay. I get it.

284
00:14:14,117 --> 00:14:16,388
I'm just happy and comfortable
to be around my family...

285
00:14:16,388 --> 00:14:17,918
after a long time,

286
00:14:18,487 --> 00:14:19,888
but Soo Yeon,

287
00:14:19,888 --> 00:14:22,487
you must be feeling uncomfortable
because of me.

288
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:24,257
That's not true, Auntie.

289
00:14:24,788 --> 00:14:27,127
I'll take good care of you
while you're staying with us.

290
00:14:27,127 --> 00:14:28,298
Please make yourself at home.

291
00:14:28,827 --> 00:14:30,398
Okay. Thanks.

292
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:33,967
Oh, right.

293
00:14:33,967 --> 00:14:36,438
Jin Dan, I heard you worked
at Angel Investments.

294
00:14:36,837 --> 00:14:37,967
Is everything going well?

295
00:14:38,007 --> 00:14:39,808
Yes. I'm working hard.

296
00:14:40,038 --> 00:14:42,548
Working hard isn't enough
to run an investment company.

297
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:44,007
You should be competent.

298
00:14:44,007 --> 00:14:45,617
You shouldn't be distracted
from your work.

299
00:14:46,048 --> 00:14:48,247
I believe
you're already well aware of that.

300
00:14:48,717 --> 00:14:49,818
Of course.

301
00:14:50,318 --> 00:14:52,288
He's doing things very well.

302
00:14:52,288 --> 00:14:54,418
All he cares about is the company.

303
00:14:54,418 --> 00:14:55,587
Of course, he should.

304
00:14:55,987 --> 00:14:59,158
You know how hard my brother worked
to grow APP Group.

305
00:14:59,257 --> 00:15:00,398
He should do well.

306
00:15:01,257 --> 00:15:02,698
Though I live in the States,

307
00:15:02,698 --> 00:15:04,698
my heart always stays here.

308
00:15:05,497 --> 00:15:08,707
Whenever I think of the company
that my brother devoted himself to...

309
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:11,367
and the future of the Gong family,

310
00:15:11,507 --> 00:15:12,977
I can't fall asleep.

311
00:15:13,107 --> 00:15:14,178
Great Auntie.

312
00:15:14,178 --> 00:15:16,577
You know
our company and our family...

313
00:15:16,577 --> 00:15:17,847
have me.

314
00:15:17,847 --> 00:15:20,617
So you should sleep well
without worrying about them.

315
00:15:20,617 --> 00:15:23,587
Insomnia isn't good for your health.

316
00:15:25,247 --> 00:15:27,058
Okay, Ma Ri.

317
00:15:27,518 --> 00:15:30,457
I wonder what lucky man
will marry our sweet Ma Ri.

318
00:15:30,457 --> 00:15:33,658
I hope he's like a handsome prince.

319
00:15:34,398 --> 00:15:36,827
I'm an independent woman,

320
00:15:36,827 --> 00:15:39,198
so I'm not waiting
for a prince to find me.

321
00:15:39,198 --> 00:15:40,497
I will find my prince...

322
00:15:40,497 --> 00:15:43,007
and bring him here myself.

323
00:15:43,768 --> 00:15:45,837
You know what?

324
00:15:45,837 --> 00:15:48,707
The dried croaker aged in barley
tastes really good.

325
00:15:48,778 --> 00:15:50,648
You like the dried croaker, right?

326
00:15:50,648 --> 00:15:52,448
- Here.
- No, I want you to eat it.

327
00:15:52,448 --> 00:15:54,018
You should eat a lot.

328
00:15:54,018 --> 00:15:56,318
My gosh. All right. Let's eat.

329
00:15:56,318 --> 00:15:57,418
Okay.

330
00:15:58,987 --> 00:16:00,288
Here. Have some.

331
00:16:16,867 --> 00:16:17,908
What's that?

332
00:16:18,168 --> 00:16:19,207
Sikhye.

333
00:16:19,438 --> 00:16:21,607
It's nice and cold.
It will help your digestion.

334
00:16:24,207 --> 00:16:26,577
I felt so uncomfortable
during the meal.

335
00:16:28,888 --> 00:16:30,747
I took digestive medicine,
but it's not helping.

336
00:16:30,747 --> 00:16:31,987
It feels like something stuck here.

337
00:16:33,388 --> 00:16:36,528
I guess your old auntie is
going to stay for long.

338
00:16:37,327 --> 00:16:38,957
This is driving me crazy.

339
00:16:40,528 --> 00:16:42,727
You should eat alone
while Auntie is staying.

340
00:16:43,428 --> 00:16:44,798
And try to avoid her
as much as you can.

341
00:16:46,798 --> 00:16:47,837
Jin Dan.

342
00:16:48,237 --> 00:16:51,068
You should focus on your work
while she stays here.

343
00:16:51,068 --> 00:16:52,737
Make sure
not to get on the wrong side of her.

344
00:16:52,737 --> 00:16:55,077
You know how obedient
your brother is to her.

345
00:16:55,448 --> 00:16:58,048
So just lay low until she leaves.

346
00:16:59,747 --> 00:17:00,778
Okay.

347
00:17:01,318 --> 00:17:03,617
You don't need to tell me
what to do.

348
00:17:05,418 --> 00:17:07,487
How much longer
do we have to live like this?

349
00:17:08,928 --> 00:17:12,658
I would've stopped putting up
with all this and moved out...

350
00:17:12,828 --> 00:17:14,527
if it weren't for Angel Investments.

351
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:19,037
I'm sorry, Jin Dan.

352
00:17:19,868 --> 00:17:21,567
That you were born as my son.

353
00:17:25,368 --> 00:17:26,408
Mom.

354
00:17:27,178 --> 00:17:28,977
Do you want
to move out of this house?

355
00:17:30,378 --> 00:17:31,948
If you're okay with it,

356
00:17:31,948 --> 00:17:33,618
I can give up
on everything right away.

357
00:17:34,477 --> 00:17:35,888
No, I don't want to.

358
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:37,688
Why would you give up on everything?
Are you crazy?

359
00:17:41,257 --> 00:17:42,257
I knew it.

360
00:17:42,787 --> 00:17:45,227
Don't worry, Mom.

361
00:17:45,928 --> 00:17:48,158
I will never let them
take what I deserve from me.

362
00:17:49,067 --> 00:17:50,727
I don't mind what I'm going through.

363
00:17:50,727 --> 00:17:53,497
So don't ever say
that you'll give up on everything.

364
00:17:53,598 --> 00:17:54,638
Okay?

365
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:56,108
I understand.

366
00:17:58,168 --> 00:18:00,807
What makes me the happiest is...

367
00:18:00,807 --> 00:18:02,277
that I was born as your son.

368
00:18:02,747 --> 00:18:04,777
That's my son.

369
00:18:04,777 --> 00:18:07,418
No wonder
why women are crazy about you.

370
00:18:09,017 --> 00:18:10,148
My sweet son.

371
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:25,428
That Park Do Ra's mom
seduced my daughter-in-law's dad...

372
00:18:25,428 --> 00:18:26,767
and took his money.

373
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:29,537
Because of Park Do Ra's mom,
the poor old man died.

374
00:18:29,537 --> 00:18:33,207
I'll go and tell everyone!

375
00:18:36,948 --> 00:18:38,578
Mom, is something wrong?

376
00:18:38,878 --> 00:18:40,317
You aren't you eating?

377
00:18:40,317 --> 00:18:42,888
What? Nothing's wrong.

378
00:18:42,888 --> 00:18:45,918
I don't feel like eating
because I've been snacking.

379
00:18:46,588 --> 00:18:49,688
What's with Jeon Baek Jo?

380
00:18:49,688 --> 00:18:51,088
There's an article
about her unsettled debt.

381
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:52,828
Her debt? Really?

382
00:18:52,828 --> 00:18:54,098
Yes. Goodness.

383
00:18:54,098 --> 00:18:55,727
She borrowed 50,000 dollars
before her debut.

384
00:18:55,727 --> 00:18:57,328
Why did she not pay it back?

385
00:18:58,227 --> 00:19:00,537
It was reported
when her career just took off.

386
00:19:01,138 --> 00:19:03,967
She's done for good.

387
00:19:04,037 --> 00:19:06,638
Why would she let
such petty money ruin her career?

388
00:19:08,108 --> 00:19:09,108
Mom.

389
00:19:09,408 --> 00:19:12,418
We don't have
any unsettled debts, do we?

390
00:19:12,977 --> 00:19:15,247
Of course not.

391
00:19:15,247 --> 00:19:17,987
It would've been a mess
if we had anything like that.

392
00:19:18,317 --> 00:19:19,317
I guess you're right.

393
00:19:22,358 --> 00:19:23,358
What?

394
00:19:28,428 --> 00:19:29,767
Why aren't you saying anything?

395
00:19:29,767 --> 00:19:32,438
Do you want me to go
to the broadcasting station tomorrow?

396
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:34,838
You know what?

397
00:19:35,497 --> 00:19:37,668
I've been snacking all day,
so I have no appetite.

398
00:19:37,668 --> 00:19:39,707
- You guys go ahead and eat.
- What?

399
00:19:39,977 --> 00:19:41,777
Why aren't you eating?
This is delicious.

400
00:19:44,608 --> 00:19:45,648
It tastes good.

401
00:19:45,878 --> 00:19:47,418
She didn't even eat much.

402
00:19:49,148 --> 00:19:51,948
This darn old lady
is driving me crazy.

403
00:19:51,948 --> 00:19:53,757
What am I supposed to do?

404
00:19:54,257 --> 00:19:55,317
My gosh.

405
00:20:00,898 --> 00:20:03,227
Please give me some time.

406
00:20:03,227 --> 00:20:05,428
I'll contact you soon.

407
00:20:07,338 --> 00:20:09,567
My goodness. Seriously...

408
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:14,378
By the way,
why isn't Do Ra's pay being wired?

409
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:18,477
What if that crazy lady
goes to the broadcasting station?

410
00:20:18,747 --> 00:20:20,717
My goodness.

411
00:20:26,457 --> 00:20:29,027
Did my muscles go into spasms
when I rolled earlier?

412
00:20:29,027 --> 00:20:30,727
Why am I so stiff and sore?

413
00:20:32,428 --> 00:20:34,957
When will "Straightforward Romance"
be finished?

414
00:20:34,997 --> 00:20:36,428
The shooting is killing me.

415
00:20:38,668 --> 00:20:41,668
No, that's not the problem.

416
00:20:42,868 --> 00:20:44,567
It should go well
so I can make my debut.

417
00:20:46,207 --> 00:20:47,237
Right.

418
00:20:48,438 --> 00:20:50,707
I should think only about
my first two-part series.

419
00:20:55,517 --> 00:20:56,648
Gosh, it hurts.

420
00:21:00,717 --> 00:21:03,727
The truth is, he followed me around
saying he had a crush on me.

421
00:21:04,588 --> 00:21:05,628
What?

422
00:21:06,128 --> 00:21:07,698
I'm his first love.

423
00:21:07,928 --> 00:21:11,198
In school, he insisted on giving me
a ride on his bike...

424
00:21:11,198 --> 00:21:13,297
and followed me around
to buy me tteokbokki.

425
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:17,207
Anyway, that's what he did.

426
00:21:18,207 --> 00:21:19,237
What?

427
00:21:19,707 --> 00:21:21,638
I had a crush on her
and followed her around?

428
00:21:22,277 --> 00:21:24,178
You've got to be kidding me.

429
00:21:25,747 --> 00:21:27,717
Park Do Ra, you brat.

430
00:21:34,457 --> 00:21:35,658
I'll do it.

431
00:21:39,198 --> 00:21:40,757
Cut! No way.

432
00:21:46,598 --> 00:21:48,997
Can he be any cuter?

433
00:21:49,668 --> 00:21:52,168
Thinking about him
just makes me laugh.

434
00:21:52,807 --> 00:21:53,908
Unbelievable.

435
00:21:59,547 --> 00:22:00,578
My gosh.

436
00:22:16,598 --> 00:22:19,567
What the...
Anyway, that was a bit weird.

437
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:21,438
I felt like I was being electrified.

438
00:22:22,608 --> 00:22:24,467
Does static electricity occur
in the woods as well?

439
00:22:30,178 --> 00:22:33,348
Why is that Curly-haired
Assistant Director so funny?

440
00:22:33,678 --> 00:22:35,618
How can you be that adorable?

441
00:22:35,618 --> 00:22:37,348
He's so adorable.

442
00:22:46,799 --> 00:22:49,539
My gosh. What has gotten into you?

443
00:22:49,739 --> 00:22:51,408
You seem to be in a good mood today.

444
00:22:51,408 --> 00:22:54,408
Aren't you tired
from all the extensive filming?

445
00:22:54,878 --> 00:22:57,208
I'm a little fatigued, but I'm fine.

446
00:22:57,208 --> 00:22:59,948
Should I make a fuss
and ease your filming schedule?

447
00:23:00,178 --> 00:23:01,848
I'm worried
this will take a toll on you.

448
00:23:01,948 --> 00:23:04,348
It'll be bad
if you faint from exhaustion.

449
00:23:04,348 --> 00:23:06,089
No, Mom. I'm good.

450
00:23:06,219 --> 00:23:08,219
I love being on set these days,

451
00:23:08,219 --> 00:23:09,858
and work has been fun.
It's all good.

452
00:23:10,019 --> 00:23:11,529
Gosh. Really?

453
00:23:11,688 --> 00:23:14,059
You've been sick and tired
of your work lately,

454
00:23:14,059 --> 00:23:15,729
and that had me worried.

455
00:23:16,299 --> 00:23:19,368
I love being on set these days,

456
00:23:19,829 --> 00:23:22,598
and this show
has brought the fun back.

457
00:23:23,039 --> 00:23:24,309
So don't worry.

458
00:23:24,309 --> 00:23:27,239
Goodness. I'm glad to hear that.

459
00:23:27,479 --> 00:23:29,408
Still, let me know if you get tired.

460
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:33,108
I'll talk to the director
and adjust your filming schedule.

461
00:23:33,178 --> 00:23:34,878
You need to be healthy...

462
00:23:34,878 --> 00:23:37,589
so that you can work
on your next project.

463
00:23:38,118 --> 00:23:39,618
Why do you say that?

464
00:23:39,618 --> 00:23:41,158
Are you worried
I won't be well enough to work?

465
00:23:41,489 --> 00:23:42,918
Then, I won't be making money.

466
00:23:43,489 --> 00:23:45,789
Why on earth
would you put it that way?

467
00:23:45,928 --> 00:23:48,398
I'm worried
you might overexert yourself.

468
00:23:48,698 --> 00:23:50,628
Gosh, you brat.

469
00:23:50,769 --> 00:23:54,168
Anyway, take this.
Drink it while on set.

470
00:23:54,168 --> 00:23:55,698
It's jujube and ginger tea.

471
00:23:55,898 --> 00:23:58,539
The weather is chilly,
and you can't have a soar throat.

472
00:23:58,569 --> 00:24:02,009
I brewed it with love
since last night.

473
00:24:02,408 --> 00:24:03,948
Got it. Thanks.

474
00:24:04,108 --> 00:24:05,779
You're the best, Mom.

475
00:24:07,918 --> 00:24:11,089
Mom, hold on.
Do you have more of this?

476
00:24:11,519 --> 00:24:13,019
Yes, I do. Why?

477
00:24:13,019 --> 00:24:14,358
Then get me an extra bottle of it.

478
00:24:14,559 --> 00:24:15,918
Sure. Hold on.

479
00:24:16,618 --> 00:24:18,958
Let me see. Here.

480
00:24:19,188 --> 00:24:21,759
Here. I already had
another bottle of it packed.

481
00:24:21,759 --> 00:24:23,329
Is it for the director?

482
00:24:23,529 --> 00:24:24,529
What?

483
00:24:25,428 --> 00:24:26,469
Yes.

484
00:24:27,168 --> 00:24:28,969
- I'll get going, then.
- Sure.

485
00:24:28,969 --> 00:24:30,969
- Thanks for this.
- No problem. Have a good one.

486
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:31,969
Got it.

487
00:24:33,979 --> 00:24:35,839
For a while, she has been
sick and tired of her work.

488
00:24:36,908 --> 00:24:40,178
Hold on. Could there be something
going on with her and Cha Bong Soo?

489
00:24:41,549 --> 00:24:44,188
Gosh, no. No way.

490
00:24:50,928 --> 00:24:52,158
Why haven't you been in touch?

491
00:24:52,989 --> 00:24:54,499
Until when do I have to wait?

492
00:24:54,729 --> 00:24:55,799
Goodness...

493
00:24:56,128 --> 00:24:59,299
What am I going to do
with this crazy old bat?

494
00:25:00,168 --> 00:25:02,668
I need to pay back the loan I own...

495
00:25:02,668 --> 00:25:04,509
and pay this old bat to shut up.

496
00:25:04,569 --> 00:25:07,239
So why isn't the head
of the production house...

497
00:25:07,239 --> 00:25:08,608
sending me the money?

498
00:25:08,608 --> 00:25:10,279
Shouldn't one keep their promise?

499
00:25:10,878 --> 00:25:12,908
Gosh. What do I do?

500
00:25:13,279 --> 00:25:14,378
What now?

501
00:25:15,148 --> 00:25:18,418
Should I ask Mr. Gong
for the money directly?

502
00:25:19,118 --> 00:25:22,559
No way. That's just wrong.

503
00:25:27,128 --> 00:25:28,128
Gosh.

504
00:25:30,729 --> 00:25:33,999
Her entire pay
was actually sent my way in full.

505
00:25:35,499 --> 00:25:36,598
The main investor...

506
00:25:36,739 --> 00:25:39,868
had to sign off on it
for the money to have been paid.

507
00:25:42,039 --> 00:25:44,648
I heard Mr. Gong was the second son
of APP Group's late chairman.

508
00:25:44,648 --> 00:25:47,049
Boy, that young man
can pull some strings.

509
00:25:47,779 --> 00:25:50,019
Goodness me.

510
00:25:55,319 --> 00:25:57,628
The current chairman of APP Group...

511
00:25:58,158 --> 00:26:00,628
only has a daughter who's ill.

512
00:26:00,658 --> 00:26:02,529
So although...

513
00:26:03,928 --> 00:26:06,098
CEO Gong Jin Dan
may be the mistress' son,

514
00:26:06,428 --> 00:26:08,269
the actual person...

515
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:11,239
to take over APP Group someday...

516
00:26:11,938 --> 00:26:14,339
Only Mr. Gong fits the bill.

517
00:26:15,779 --> 00:26:16,938
On top of that,

518
00:26:17,549 --> 00:26:19,479
he's an unmarried single man.

519
00:26:20,049 --> 00:26:22,219
Mr. Gong, it's nothing big.

520
00:26:22,219 --> 00:26:25,049
I'm sure you have everything
the world can offer,

521
00:26:25,049 --> 00:26:27,918
but one wears a different necktie
every day.

522
00:26:28,358 --> 00:26:30,388
This seemed to suit you
which is why Do Ra and I...

523
00:26:30,388 --> 00:26:31,858
picked it out together.

524
00:26:31,989 --> 00:26:34,999
Gosh. Really?
Ms. Park picked it out?

525
00:26:34,999 --> 00:26:35,999
That's right.

526
00:26:36,128 --> 00:26:38,128
She wanted to come with me
to see you today,

527
00:26:38,128 --> 00:26:39,898
but she couldn't get away
from the set.

528
00:26:39,898 --> 00:26:41,769
I came on her behalf.

529
00:26:42,398 --> 00:26:45,809
Mr. Gong, thank you so much.

530
00:26:45,969 --> 00:26:48,539
You had Do Ra's pay
made out in advance.

531
00:26:48,638 --> 00:26:51,208
I'm well aware
that you signed off on it...

532
00:26:51,208 --> 00:26:52,608
to make it happen.

533
00:26:52,608 --> 00:26:54,279
Gosh, that was nothing.

534
00:26:54,979 --> 00:26:56,219
It's like I said.

535
00:26:56,648 --> 00:26:59,019
While Ms. Park
is filming this series,

536
00:26:59,019 --> 00:27:00,759
I won't let her be bothered
by anything else.

537
00:27:01,289 --> 00:27:04,059
She'll be able to stay focused
solely on her work.

538
00:27:04,289 --> 00:27:07,628
My gosh, Mr. Gong.
You are an impressive man.

539
00:27:07,628 --> 00:27:09,198
Thank you so much.

540
00:27:11,368 --> 00:27:12,928
- Please excuse me.
- Sure.

541
00:27:16,438 --> 00:27:18,668
I can't wait any longer.

542
00:27:18,839 --> 00:27:20,938
I'm getting ready
to head to the broadcasting station.

543
00:27:21,178 --> 00:27:22,309
What will it be?

544
00:27:23,039 --> 00:27:25,208
What's wrong? Is something up?

545
00:27:26,579 --> 00:27:29,519
Gosh, no. It's nothing.

546
00:27:29,549 --> 00:27:31,448
My daughter being a celebrity...

547
00:27:31,448 --> 00:27:34,688
leads to all kinds of flies
swarming around us.

548
00:27:34,918 --> 00:27:37,958
Please let me know
if there's anything I can do.

549
00:27:39,029 --> 00:27:41,898
We can't have flies
swarming around Ms. Park.

550
00:27:43,458 --> 00:27:46,168
Your offer to help alone
has my heart filled with gratitude.

551
00:27:48,569 --> 00:27:51,208
That crazy old bat.
Should I just kill you?

552
00:27:51,438 --> 00:27:53,168
You have another thing coming.

553
00:27:55,608 --> 00:27:57,579
What was that? 40,000 dollars?

554
00:27:58,779 --> 00:28:00,309
Did you just say 40,000 dollars?

555
00:28:01,678 --> 00:28:04,448
It's as I explained the other day.

556
00:28:04,448 --> 00:28:06,719
I didn't borrow
the 30,000 dollars from him.

557
00:28:06,749 --> 00:28:09,888
Mr. Kim gave it to me to spend.

558
00:28:10,628 --> 00:28:13,329
So technically,
I don't have to pay anyone back.

559
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:16,198
However, to save Do Ra's face,

560
00:28:16,198 --> 00:28:19,198
I am extending a generous offer...

561
00:28:19,198 --> 00:28:20,638
by adding 10,000 dollars
in interest.

562
00:28:20,638 --> 00:28:21,698
Look here.

563
00:28:21,698 --> 00:28:24,039
My daughter-in-law's father died
because of you,

564
00:28:24,509 --> 00:28:27,279
and she has been heartbroken
ever since.

565
00:28:28,079 --> 00:28:29,509
My gosh.

566
00:28:29,509 --> 00:28:32,509
But rather than paying more
as compensation, you...

567
00:28:34,948 --> 00:28:36,648
Fine. Then,

568
00:28:37,418 --> 00:28:40,289
I'll settle for twice the principal
which is 60,000 dollars.

569
00:28:42,589 --> 00:28:45,589
I never took you as one,
but you are a conniving thief.

570
00:28:47,299 --> 00:28:50,729
If you keep this up,
I'll report you for blackmailing.

571
00:28:50,868 --> 00:28:53,329
Go ahead
and tell people I owe you money.

572
00:28:53,598 --> 00:28:54,938
What? Fine.

573
00:28:55,469 --> 00:28:58,638
We'll meet each other halfway.

574
00:29:01,908 --> 00:29:04,708
How about 50,000 dollars?
Is that good enough?

575
00:29:10,479 --> 00:29:11,549
Fine.

576
00:29:14,158 --> 00:29:16,089
Then, here...

577
00:29:17,589 --> 00:29:19,888
You will write
a memorandum in exchange.

578
00:29:20,128 --> 00:29:21,428
A memorandum?

579
00:29:21,428 --> 00:29:23,628
I can't have you harassing me again.

580
00:29:23,628 --> 00:29:25,598
We should end it right here.

581
00:29:26,398 --> 00:29:28,299
Write the memorandum,

582
00:29:28,598 --> 00:29:30,198
and I'll wire the money
straight away.

583
00:29:31,208 --> 00:29:32,269
Fine.

584
00:29:33,069 --> 00:29:34,138
I'll write one.

585
00:29:35,908 --> 00:29:37,448
