677
00:33:48,861 --> 00:33:51,690
Gosh. Was the door locked?

678
00:33:51,690 --> 00:33:54,601
That must be due
to the house being rusty.

679
00:33:54,601 --> 00:33:56,901
We should renovate sometime.

680
00:33:56,901 --> 00:34:00,770
The door locks on its own
every now and again.

681
00:34:00,871 --> 00:34:03,101
- Yes, that happens.
- Right.

682
00:34:03,101 --> 00:34:04,811
- We should renovate.
- I see.

683
00:34:06,770 --> 00:34:07,841
Right.

684
00:34:15,750 --> 00:34:18,821
What were they up to
behind that locked door?

685
00:34:21,460 --> 00:34:22,761
I don't care though.

686
00:34:22,761 --> 00:34:25,261
I can't let him take out
more loans against this house.

687
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:26,861
Never.

688
00:34:30,661 --> 00:34:32,431
Okay, good.

689
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:42,140
I got it.

690
00:34:48,951 --> 00:34:50,151
Have it gift-wrapped.

691
00:34:51,620 --> 00:34:53,321
- Make it look pretty.
- Sure.

692
00:34:57,321 --> 00:35:00,361
Of course.
Every woman loves diamonds.

693
00:35:01,201 --> 00:35:04,330
This will be enough
to charm Park Do Ra's pants off.

694
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:07,971
I wonder if she's filming.

695
00:35:09,870 --> 00:35:10,971
Hold on.

696
00:35:12,071 --> 00:35:13,540
If I approach her too suddenly,

697
00:35:13,540 --> 00:35:15,611
she might think of me
as a crazy person.

698
00:35:16,781 --> 00:35:19,011
She's a precious soul,
and I should be respectful.

699
00:35:19,451 --> 00:35:20,651
Gradually,

700
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:23,321
like a light drizzle
that goes unnoticed.

701
00:35:23,980 --> 00:35:27,690
I'll have her become
head over heels for me.

702
00:35:29,020 --> 00:35:30,261
Diamonds it is.

703
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:35,131
How could you do this to me?

704
00:35:39,170 --> 00:35:41,870
You punk. Yesterday, you...

