784
00:38:55,761 --> 00:38:57,301
Of course. Absolutely.

785
00:38:57,301 --> 00:38:58,500
Promise me that.

786
00:38:58,500 --> 00:38:59,500
I promise.

787
00:39:00,770 --> 00:39:02,040
Ms. Park.

788
00:39:02,301 --> 00:39:05,540
Have some spicy tteokbokki
and lighten up.

789
00:39:05,540 --> 00:39:07,571
I bought it at the market.

790
00:39:08,241 --> 00:39:10,140
They sell the best tteokbokki.

791
00:39:10,781 --> 00:39:12,881
Here. Have some while it's warm.

792
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:14,850
Thank you.

793
00:39:23,821 --> 00:39:26,631
No way. This is to die for.

794
00:39:26,631 --> 00:39:28,201
Right? Isn't it good?

795
00:39:29,060 --> 00:39:32,170
Seeing you enjoy it
makes the trip worthwhile.

796
00:39:33,971 --> 00:39:35,071
Hold on a second.

797
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:37,201
Here it is.

798
00:39:37,741 --> 00:39:38,741
Ta-da.

799
00:39:41,681 --> 00:39:42,681
Here.

800
00:39:44,580 --> 00:39:46,480
Try this.
It's jujube and ginger tea.

801
00:39:48,821 --> 00:39:50,250
It smells incredible.

802
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:56,591
Gosh. No way.

803
00:39:56,591 --> 00:39:57,591
Isn't it good?

804
00:39:57,591 --> 00:40:00,591
It tastes like
the jujube and ginger...

805
00:40:00,790 --> 00:40:02,901
don't clash with the other flavor,

806
00:40:03,201 --> 00:40:04,401
and they mesh well together.

807
00:40:06,330 --> 00:40:10,401
I got up early this morning
and made it myself.

808
00:40:10,571 --> 00:40:12,040
For you, Mr. Ko.

809
00:40:12,471 --> 00:40:15,140
So drink it all. Every single drop.

810
00:40:15,310 --> 00:40:16,810
It's really good for you.

811
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:20,911
Gosh. This is an honor. Thank you.

812
00:40:24,750 --> 00:40:26,850
Goodness. It warms me up.

813
00:40:27,790 --> 00:40:29,120
The tteokbokki's amazing.

814
00:40:31,020 --> 00:40:32,431
How did it go, Pil Seung?

815
00:40:33,161 --> 00:40:34,361
Did you do damage control?

816
00:40:36,631 --> 00:40:38,401
I soothed Park Do Ra
with tteokbokki.

817
00:40:39,531 --> 00:40:41,270
Fried chicken for Cha Bong Soo.

818
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:43,701
You know,

819
00:40:44,370 --> 00:40:47,370
Working with the grumpy actors...

820
00:40:47,471 --> 00:40:48,681
is just killing me.

821
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:53,651
Pil Seung.
What would I have done without you?

822
00:40:53,881 --> 00:40:55,551
You will make a great director.

823
00:40:57,080 --> 00:40:59,321
Your praise doesn't console me.

824
00:40:59,951 --> 00:41:00,951
Pil Seung.

825
00:41:01,821 --> 00:41:03,721
I need this drama to succeed.

826
00:41:03,991 --> 00:41:05,761
I want to do a really good job.

827
00:41:06,591 --> 00:41:08,761
But if those grumps
fight once more,

828
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,431
the shock might kill me.

829
00:41:12,471 --> 00:41:13,600
So, Pil Seung.

830
00:41:14,471 --> 00:41:16,270
Don't run away.

831
00:41:16,670 --> 00:41:19,071
Stay right by my side and help me.

832
00:41:19,071 --> 00:41:21,170
If this drama does well,
it won't just benefit me.

833
00:41:21,170 --> 00:41:22,381
It'll benefit you too.

834
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:26,151
Jin Gu. Don't worry.

835
00:41:27,111 --> 00:41:29,051
Whatever it takes, I'll see to it...

836
00:41:29,881 --> 00:41:30,951
that we finish the project.

837
00:41:31,551 --> 00:41:32,620
Okay.

838
00:41:33,721 --> 00:41:34,861
I believe in you.

839
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:49,571
This is for you.

840
00:41:50,940 --> 00:41:51,940
Goodness.

841
00:41:52,841 --> 00:41:55,710
Curly-haired Director.
What are the flowers for?

842
00:41:55,810 --> 00:41:57,911
I was so grateful
for the jujube and ginger tea.

843
00:41:59,310 --> 00:42:01,181
It was nothing at all.

844
00:42:01,181 --> 00:42:02,520
It wasn't nothing.

845
00:42:02,520 --> 00:42:05,290
Who could dream of having
jujube and ginger tea you made?

846
00:42:06,451 --> 00:42:07,551
You're right.

847
00:42:08,161 --> 00:42:11,261
Despite the difficult situations
and problems,

848
00:42:11,261 --> 00:42:14,031
you work so hard out of love
and care for our project.

849
00:42:14,031 --> 00:42:15,201
I'm so thankful.

850
00:42:15,460 --> 00:42:17,730
You even held back
when Bong Soo had an outburst.

851
00:42:17,901 --> 00:42:19,131
And you trusted me.

852
00:42:19,330 --> 00:42:22,670
Compared to the gratitude I feel,
these flowers are a small gesture.

853
00:42:22,670 --> 00:42:24,170
Not at all.

854
00:42:24,841 --> 00:42:27,571
I'm so moved.

855
00:42:27,571 --> 00:42:28,980
Thanks so much.

856
00:42:29,710 --> 00:42:33,051
From now on, even if Bong Soo
loses his mind, I won't react.

857
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:34,850
I'll think of the flowers.

858
00:42:36,881 --> 00:42:37,881
Thank you.

859
00:42:38,951 --> 00:42:40,620
Since taking on this project,

860
00:42:41,520 --> 00:42:43,361
I've learned a lot.

861
00:42:44,290 --> 00:42:45,531
Come on.

862
00:42:46,190 --> 00:42:47,690
You're welcome.

863
00:42:49,631 --> 00:42:51,801
If you cast me
in your directorial debut,

864
00:42:51,801 --> 00:42:54,301
I'll take the role
without any conditions or demands.

865
00:42:54,301 --> 00:42:55,600
I swear.

866
00:42:56,341 --> 00:42:57,640
- You will?
- Yes.

867
00:42:57,770 --> 00:42:59,770
That's an honor. Thank you.

868
00:43:00,040 --> 00:43:02,681
You have just one more scene today.
Get ready to film.

869
00:43:03,111 --> 00:43:04,111
Okay.

870
00:43:05,551 --> 00:43:06,681
They're beautiful.

871
00:43:10,109 --> 00:43:12,038
Goodness. Son.

872
00:43:12,239 --> 00:43:14,948
I haven't seen you
in a suit in a while.

873
00:43:14,948 --> 00:43:16,978
You look amazing.

874
00:43:19,388 --> 00:43:20,448
Honey.

875
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:22,719
Why are you in a suit?

876
00:43:23,018 --> 00:43:24,388
Who are you meeting?

877
00:43:25,058 --> 00:43:27,529
I'll tell you some other time.

878
00:43:28,529 --> 00:43:31,228
Who are you meeting
that you'll tell me another time?

879
00:43:31,928 --> 00:43:35,098
They're not weirdos who want you
to start a business, are they?

880
00:43:35,169 --> 00:43:36,169
No.

881
00:43:36,469 --> 00:43:37,638
Hey, Sun Young.

882
00:43:38,299 --> 00:43:40,069
Why would you say that?

883
00:43:40,509 --> 00:43:42,209
My Hyun Chul isn't a fool.

884
00:43:42,209 --> 00:43:44,178
He wouldn't go around meeting weirdos.

885
00:43:45,678 --> 00:43:49,319
The man of the house wore a suit
for the first time in a while.

886
00:43:49,478 --> 00:43:52,649
You should just say,
"You look great. Have a nice day."

887
00:43:55,919 --> 00:43:57,118
Ko Myung Dong.

888
00:43:57,859 --> 00:44:00,689
Did you spend the night elsewhere?

889
00:44:00,928 --> 00:44:02,828
Why are you doing stuff
you never did before?

890
00:44:03,299 --> 00:44:05,029
Come here. Did you drink last night?

891
00:44:05,029 --> 00:44:06,328
- Leave her alone.
- Hey.

892
00:44:06,969 --> 00:44:10,399
You know her friend Jang Mi.

893
00:44:10,739 --> 00:44:14,138
She's been having a terrible time
since she got divorced.

894
00:44:14,239 --> 00:44:15,978
Myung Dong wanted to be with her.

895
00:44:15,978 --> 00:44:19,678
I told you to spend
a few nights with her.

896
00:44:20,009 --> 00:44:21,279
So...

897
00:44:22,748 --> 00:44:25,678
Is Jang Mi feeling better now?

898
00:44:26,448 --> 00:44:27,448
What?

899
00:44:29,049 --> 00:44:31,359
Yes. I guess?

900
00:44:31,819 --> 00:44:33,058
Goodness.

901
00:44:33,529 --> 00:44:37,399
Still, you should sleep
in your own bed.

902
00:44:38,029 --> 00:44:40,799
- See you later. I'm off, Mom.
- But...

903
00:44:46,169 --> 00:44:48,868
(Park Do Sik)

904
00:44:52,609 --> 00:44:53,908
Let's meet.

905
00:44:54,308 --> 00:44:55,509
I have something to say.

906
00:44:55,748 --> 00:44:57,879
It's not right to end it like this.

907
00:44:58,419 --> 00:44:59,989
This woman, honestly...

908
00:45:01,489 --> 00:45:02,859
Is she a leech or what?

909
00:45:04,689 --> 00:45:08,029
What does she want to talk about?
She's driving me insane.

910
00:45:09,799 --> 00:45:11,129
What did you want to say?

911
00:45:12,868 --> 00:45:14,899
I waited for a long time,

912
00:45:16,368 --> 00:45:18,739
but now I'm too impatient to wait.

913
00:45:20,209 --> 00:45:21,339
For what?

914
00:45:22,779 --> 00:45:24,908
Do you still have a regular period?

915
00:45:26,448 --> 00:45:27,478
What?

916
00:45:28,709 --> 00:45:30,719
You're getting older too.

917
00:45:31,578 --> 00:45:34,049
So how about you see a doctor...

918
00:45:34,049 --> 00:45:36,089
and get some medical help?

919
00:45:36,189 --> 00:45:37,388
Before it's too late.

920
00:45:38,589 --> 00:45:42,489
What are you talking about, Auntie?

921
00:45:42,629 --> 00:45:44,129
I'm talking about a child.

922
00:45:46,768 --> 00:45:49,098
A son would be great,
but a daughter's okay too.

923
00:45:50,239 --> 00:45:51,899
You know Ma Ri's state.

924
00:45:52,739 --> 00:45:54,908
Before it's too late,
you must have a child...

925
00:45:55,138 --> 00:45:57,209
to carry on the family and company.

926
00:45:58,678 --> 00:46:00,709
You're still young and healthy.

927
00:46:02,609 --> 00:46:06,018
Auntie. I turn 60 soon.

928
00:46:06,919 --> 00:46:08,689
I don't have periods anymore.

929
00:46:09,018 --> 00:46:10,158
I haven't for a while.

930
00:46:11,259 --> 00:46:13,359
Why are you telling me that now?

931
00:46:14,089 --> 00:46:15,089
What?

932
00:46:15,228 --> 00:46:17,828
I thought you could still do
your womanly duty.

933
00:46:18,598 --> 00:46:19,629
What?

934
00:46:25,969 --> 00:46:27,469
What's up with her?

935
00:46:28,239 --> 00:46:30,839
Was she waiting for me
to get pregnant all this time?

936
00:46:31,138 --> 00:46:32,779
My goodness.

937
00:46:33,149 --> 00:46:35,709
At my age? That's nonsense.

938
00:46:38,448 --> 00:46:39,888
Oh, gosh.

939
00:46:40,049 --> 00:46:42,348
Where's the housekeeper? Ma'am?

940
00:46:42,348 --> 00:46:44,158
Yes? I'm here.

941
00:46:44,158 --> 00:46:45,189
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

942
00:46:45,189 --> 00:46:47,428
I asked you to change my sheets.
Why are they the same?

943
00:46:47,828 --> 00:46:49,189
You didn't clean my bathroom either.

944
00:46:50,359 --> 00:46:51,998
Sorry. I'll do that tomorrow.

945
00:46:51,998 --> 00:46:54,198
Ma'am. What are you thinking?

946
00:46:54,569 --> 00:46:56,268
Who says
you can decide to do it tomorrow?

947
00:46:57,498 --> 00:46:59,299
Are you belittling me too now?

948
00:46:59,609 --> 00:47:01,609
Why would I belittle you?

949
00:47:02,109 --> 00:47:03,509
It's not that.

950
00:47:03,739 --> 00:47:06,038
Madam Jang told me
to clean Madam Gong's bathroom...

951
00:47:06,038 --> 00:47:07,649
and Ma Ri's room first,

952
00:47:07,649 --> 00:47:09,578
and if I didn't have the time
to clean the second madam's room,

953
00:47:09,578 --> 00:47:11,248
I could do it tomorrow.

954
00:47:11,248 --> 00:47:13,319
What? I'm the second madam?

955
00:47:13,919 --> 00:47:15,888
Who says you can call me that?

956
00:47:16,359 --> 00:47:18,989
Who told you
to call me "second madam?"

957
00:47:19,219 --> 00:47:21,928
Hong Ae Kyo. What are you doing?

958
00:47:22,629 --> 00:47:25,098
Why are you shouting at Ms. Yeoju?

959
00:47:25,098 --> 00:47:28,598
Jang Soo Yeon.
How dare you call me by name?

960
00:47:28,799 --> 00:47:31,239
She looks down on me
because you're like this.

961
00:47:31,339 --> 00:47:33,138
What's going on here?

962
00:47:38,209 --> 00:47:39,879
What's the matter?

963
00:47:40,908 --> 00:47:42,748
What are you arguing about now?

964
00:47:43,748 --> 00:47:46,419
Yes. I'm a mistress.

965
00:47:47,419 --> 00:47:50,919
But I bore the late chairman a son.

966
00:47:51,689 --> 00:47:53,459
On his death bed,
he acknowledged me...

967
00:47:53,759 --> 00:47:55,959
as the mother of his son.

968
00:47:56,899 --> 00:47:58,728
But she looks down on me.

969
00:47:59,328 --> 00:48:01,598
So much so that
even the hired help belittles me.

970
00:48:02,268 --> 00:48:04,138
Any culture would say this is wrong.

971
00:48:05,198 --> 00:48:07,768
I know you were friends
who went to high school together,

972
00:48:07,939 --> 00:48:09,578
but a mother-in-law
and daughter-in-law...

973
00:48:09,578 --> 00:48:11,839
shouldn't fight and call each other
by name.

974
00:48:12,408 --> 00:48:13,848
What kind of mess is this?

975
00:48:15,109 --> 00:48:16,149
Chairman Gong.

976
00:48:16,549 --> 00:48:19,448
Is our family
that uneducated and low-class?

977
00:48:26,888 --> 00:48:30,558
When I heard my older brother
had had a child with a woman...

978
00:48:30,558 --> 00:48:32,228
young enough to be his daughter,

979
00:48:32,899 --> 00:48:34,228
I didn't get it.

980
00:48:35,598 --> 00:48:37,299
I was embarrassed, and I hated it.

981
00:48:39,198 --> 00:48:42,169
Jin Taek, your late mother.

982
00:48:42,609 --> 00:48:45,609
I felt so sorry and guilty for her.

983
00:48:46,379 --> 00:48:48,078
I was that ashamed.

984
00:48:49,448 --> 00:48:50,448
However,

985
00:48:51,149 --> 00:48:53,618
even though our family
did some unorthodox things,

986
00:48:53,618 --> 00:48:55,018
we can't be like this.

987
00:48:56,689 --> 00:48:58,359
She was your father's wife.

988
00:48:58,788 --> 00:49:00,888
She even gave birth
to your father's son, after all.

989
00:49:01,689 --> 00:49:04,029
She should be treated
with due respect.

990
00:49:04,029 --> 00:49:05,598
What kind of mess is this?

991
00:49:07,469 --> 00:49:10,138
Listen, Jin Taek and Soo Yeon.

992
00:49:11,469 --> 00:49:13,908
From this moment forward,
you will call her Mother.

993
00:49:15,368 --> 00:49:16,808
Auntie.

994
00:49:16,808 --> 00:49:18,279
I understand it's awkward...

995
00:49:18,279 --> 00:49:19,649
since you went
to high school together.

996
00:49:20,678 --> 00:49:23,549
But this is just wrong.

997
00:49:25,279 --> 00:49:28,919
Once Jin Dan and Ma Ri get married,
we will have new family members.

998
00:49:29,689 --> 00:49:31,388
I don't want you...

999
00:49:31,589 --> 00:49:34,189
to call each other by name
and fight like this around them.

1000
00:49:35,728 --> 00:49:38,598
Our family isn't so ignorant.

1001
00:49:39,498 --> 00:49:42,328
Even if she was younger than you,

1002
00:49:42,899 --> 00:49:44,969
you should've called her Mother.

1003
00:49:46,469 --> 00:49:47,569
Don't you think so?

1004
00:49:51,339 --> 00:49:52,578
Okay.

1005
00:49:53,509 --> 00:49:55,009
We will do as you say.

1006
00:49:58,879 --> 00:49:59,948
I'm sorry...

1007
00:50:02,219 --> 00:50:03,589
for everything.

1008
00:50:07,328 --> 00:50:08,759
Mother.

1009
00:50:14,129 --> 00:50:15,198
Ma Ri.

1010
00:50:15,669 --> 00:50:17,399
Yes, Great Auntie.

1011
00:50:17,839 --> 00:50:20,839
You should call her Grandmother now.

1012
00:50:20,908 --> 00:50:21,908
Okay?

1013
00:50:22,239 --> 00:50:24,538
She doesn't like it
when I call her Grandmother.

1014
00:50:24,739 --> 00:50:27,509
No, I don't mind it.
You can call me Grandmother.

1015
00:50:29,549 --> 00:50:30,578
Ms. Yeoju.

1016
00:50:30,848 --> 00:50:32,219
Yes, Madam Gong.

1017
00:50:32,219 --> 00:50:35,419
You should think of her
as the first madam...

1018
00:50:35,419 --> 00:50:38,189
and Ma Ri's mom as the second.

1019
00:50:41,859 --> 00:50:43,129
Please do as you're told.

1020
00:50:44,859 --> 00:50:46,728
Yes, I understand.

1021
00:50:54,109 --> 00:50:57,178
Auntie has no right
to tell us what to do in the house.

1022
00:50:59,279 --> 00:51:01,549
She's the oldest member
of our family.

1023
00:51:02,078 --> 00:51:03,478
She's an aunt,

1024
00:51:03,978 --> 00:51:06,319
but she's like my mother to me.

1025
00:51:08,189 --> 00:51:11,518
She raised me
when my mother was ill in bed.

1026
00:51:12,759 --> 00:51:16,828
If she hadn't given me her liver
when I was little,

1027
00:51:16,959 --> 00:51:18,728
I wouldn't have made it this far.

1028
00:51:18,728 --> 00:51:20,498
And you know that.

1029
00:51:20,629 --> 00:51:22,598
Still, this is unacceptable.

1030
00:51:22,998 --> 00:51:25,799
Why do you always do as she says?

1031
00:51:25,998 --> 00:51:29,138
It's not like I do as she says.
That's just the right thing to do.

1032
00:51:32,609 --> 00:51:34,478
It's true that I was wrong.

1033
00:51:36,109 --> 00:51:37,719
Like Auntie said,

1034
00:51:37,848 --> 00:51:40,448
even if she was younger than you,

1035
00:51:44,189 --> 00:51:46,259
we should call her Mother.

1036
00:51:48,259 --> 00:51:49,428
I can't.

1037
00:51:50,959 --> 00:51:52,158
You can't?

1038
00:51:53,169 --> 00:51:55,228
Then what are you going to do?

1039
00:51:55,598 --> 00:51:57,569
Do you think this is easy for me?

1040
00:52:01,908 --> 00:52:02,939
Honey.

1041
00:52:17,359 --> 00:52:18,618
Yes, Ae Kyo.

1042
00:52:21,689 --> 00:52:22,689
Hey.

1043
00:52:24,058 --> 00:52:26,498
Ae Kyo, what brings you here?

1044
00:52:28,969 --> 00:52:32,069
I'll treat you as my sister-in-law
from now on.

1045
00:52:33,339 --> 00:52:34,339
What?

1046
00:52:35,868 --> 00:52:37,078
Wait.

1047
00:52:37,078 --> 00:52:39,638
Ae Kyo, what are you doing?
Get up this instant.

1048
00:52:40,509 --> 00:52:41,549
Dae Sook.

1049
00:52:42,908 --> 00:52:46,248
Thank you for clearing things up
about how we address each other.

1050
00:52:48,189 --> 00:52:50,489
I met the late chairman
when I was 21.

1051
00:52:51,359 --> 00:52:54,428
He's the only man
I've ever been with.

1052
00:52:56,428 --> 00:52:58,399
And I had a son with him.

1053
00:52:59,158 --> 00:53:01,529
I've spent my whole life
trying to raise my son,

1054
00:53:01,529 --> 00:53:03,339
Gong Jin Dan well.

1055
00:53:06,439 --> 00:53:08,368
The only thing I did wrong...

1056
00:53:10,138 --> 00:53:13,549
is that I met the late chairman
knowing he was married...

1057
00:53:16,649 --> 00:53:18,649
and that I had his son.

1058
00:53:20,989 --> 00:53:23,919
Yes, I know I'm a sinner.

1059
00:53:26,759 --> 00:53:29,058
And yet you accepted me...

1060
00:53:29,689 --> 00:53:32,029
and covered for me
despite what I did.

1061
00:53:32,828 --> 00:53:35,029
I'm really grateful to you.

1062
00:53:37,799 --> 00:53:39,239
I will do...

1063
00:53:40,469 --> 00:53:43,379
whatever you tell me to do now.

1064
00:53:45,078 --> 00:53:47,149
You helped me resolve
my deep sorrow.

1065
00:53:48,879 --> 00:53:51,149
I can even use my hair
to make straw shoes for you.

1066
00:53:52,018 --> 00:53:54,518
I'll make sure
to repay your kindness.

1067
00:53:56,388 --> 00:53:57,459
Dae Sook.

1068
00:53:58,788 --> 00:54:01,288
I hope you live
a long and healthy life.

1069
00:54:02,859 --> 00:54:05,759
All right. I know what you mean.
That's enough.

1070
00:54:05,759 --> 00:54:07,629
Come on. Get up now.

1071
00:54:09,169 --> 00:54:10,469
My gosh.

1072
00:54:10,868 --> 00:54:12,538
Dae Sook...

1073
00:54:12,598 --> 00:54:13,609
All right.

1074
00:54:15,239 --> 00:54:16,339
Dae Sook.

1075
00:54:23,448 --> 00:54:25,279
I know how you're feeling.

1076
00:54:25,279 --> 00:54:27,319
That's enough. Stop crying.

1077
00:54:28,618 --> 00:54:29,888
I understand.

1078
00:54:30,859 --> 00:54:32,189
Thank you.

1079
00:54:35,928 --> 00:54:36,928
What?

1080
00:54:41,598 --> 00:54:43,899
The Curly-haired Assistant Director
always wears a backpack.

1081
00:54:44,698 --> 00:54:45,899
This must look good on him.

1082
00:54:47,109 --> 00:54:48,209
Are you buying a backpack?

1083
00:54:48,509 --> 00:54:49,509
Yes.

1084
00:54:49,739 --> 00:54:50,808
Hey, do you think...

1085
00:54:50,808 --> 00:54:53,138
the Curly-haired Assistant Director
will like this?

1086
00:54:54,149 --> 00:54:55,279
Do Ra.

1087
00:54:55,279 --> 00:54:57,848
Are you buying this designer bag
for the assistant director?

1088
00:54:57,848 --> 00:54:58,919
Yes.

1089
00:54:59,319 --> 00:55:01,919
He's given me many things,
so I want to thank him.

1090
00:55:01,989 --> 00:55:02,989
Come on.

1091
00:55:02,989 --> 00:55:05,359
You just got some tteokbokki
and two-dollar ice cream.

1092
00:55:05,359 --> 00:55:07,489
Don't you think
a designer bag is too much?

1093
00:55:08,959 --> 00:55:10,698
- You think so?
- Yes.

1094
00:55:10,698 --> 00:55:13,669
And you should get one
for Director Hong as well.

1095
00:55:13,669 --> 00:55:16,029
I'm sure
Director Hong will be upset...

1096
00:55:16,029 --> 00:55:18,138
if he finds out that
only Assistant Director Ko got this.

1097
00:55:18,399 --> 00:55:19,939
- Really?
- Yes.

1098
00:55:19,939 --> 00:55:22,239
If you want to get him something,

1099
00:55:22,239 --> 00:55:24,779
what about a hat like this?

1100
00:55:25,439 --> 00:55:26,709
Just go with this hat.

1101
00:55:32,719 --> 00:55:33,719
Come on.

1102
00:55:47,828 --> 00:55:49,328
I hope this navy hat...

1103
00:55:49,828 --> 00:55:51,939
will look good
on Curly-haired Assistant Director.

1104
00:55:56,439 --> 00:55:58,239
Should I give him this
in this shopping bag?

1105
00:55:58,239 --> 00:55:59,978
Or should I put this on his head?

1106
00:56:03,549 --> 00:56:05,578
Gosh, no.

1107
00:56:05,578 --> 00:56:09,049
If I put this on him,
he might get the wrong idea.

1108
00:56:09,049 --> 00:56:11,359
I should give him this in the bag.

1109
00:56:14,558 --> 00:56:15,558
What?

1110
00:56:18,859 --> 00:56:19,959
Gosh.

1111
00:56:21,629 --> 00:56:22,828
Oh, dear.

1112
00:56:24,939 --> 00:56:25,969
What's wrong?

1113
00:56:26,098 --> 00:56:27,839
Do Ra, listen.

1114
00:56:28,439 --> 00:56:31,109
I don't want you to give this hat
to the Curly-haired Assistant Director.

1115
00:56:31,109 --> 00:56:32,209
Why not?

1116
00:56:32,209 --> 00:56:34,978
That Curly-haired Assistant Director
is a lot worse than I thought.

1117
00:56:34,978 --> 00:56:37,649
He keeps switching sides like a bat.

1118
00:56:38,149 --> 00:56:39,978
A bat? What do you mean?

1119
00:56:39,978 --> 00:56:43,319
The Curly-haired Assistant Director
is talking behind your back...

1120
00:56:44,788 --> 00:56:46,558
with Cha Bong Soo,
the garlic pervert.

1121
00:56:49,189 --> 00:56:50,328
Hey.

1122
00:56:50,629 --> 00:56:53,299
That's just ridiculous.

1123
00:56:54,669 --> 00:56:57,439
That's the last thing
Assistant Director Ko would do.

1124
00:56:57,498 --> 00:56:58,939
Who told you that?

1125
00:56:58,939 --> 00:57:01,469
Even now, they are
criticizing you behind your back.

1126
00:57:01,908 --> 00:57:04,308
While he got you
five-dollar tteokbokki,

1127
00:57:04,308 --> 00:57:07,178
he bought Cha Bong Soo
chicken, pizza, and beer.

1128
00:57:07,178 --> 00:57:09,078
Yesterday, he even went
to a fish market...

1129
00:57:09,078 --> 00:57:11,779
and bought raw fish
for Cha Bong Soo to flatter him.

1130
00:57:11,779 --> 00:57:12,848
Lee Jae Dong.

1131
00:57:12,848 --> 00:57:15,288
Curly-haired Assistant Director
isn't that kind of person.

1132
00:57:15,819 --> 00:57:18,419
I think someone just made it up.

1133
00:57:18,419 --> 00:57:19,759
Don't listen to them.

1134
00:57:19,759 --> 00:57:21,888
And do you not remember
what I told you?

1135
00:57:21,888 --> 00:57:25,259
You should cover your eyes and ears
while you're at work.

1136
00:57:25,629 --> 00:57:26,728
Just keep your mouth shut.

1137
00:57:27,129 --> 00:57:29,969
Don't you ever say anything silly
like that again, okay?

1138
00:57:29,969 --> 00:57:31,498
- But from what I heard...
- Shush.

1139
00:57:33,198 --> 00:57:34,339
Okay.

1140
00:57:51,219 --> 00:57:52,788
Is spring coming?

1141
00:57:53,759 --> 00:57:55,359
The weather is crazy.

1142
00:57:56,489 --> 00:57:57,928
It's insane.

1143
00:58:16,009 --> 00:58:17,948
Doesn't she have her own hands?

1144
00:58:18,518 --> 00:58:20,618
Why would she let him tidy her hair?

1145
00:58:24,288 --> 00:58:25,319
No.

1146
00:58:26,589 --> 00:58:29,828
This is all about romance.

1147
00:58:30,899 --> 00:58:34,129
I have my own hands,
but I let him tidy my hair.

1148
00:58:37,868 --> 00:58:39,038
I'm jealous.

1149
00:58:48,379 --> 00:58:51,078
All right. I'll do it one last time.

1150
00:58:51,748 --> 00:58:53,319
I'll call him one last time.

1151
00:58:53,948 --> 00:58:55,618
My pride doesn't matter now.

1152
00:58:57,189 --> 00:58:58,919
(The Wednesday Man)

1153
00:59:00,489 --> 00:59:02,959
The number you have dialed
does not exist.

1154
00:59:03,388 --> 00:59:04,658
- Please check the number...
- What?

1155
00:59:04,658 --> 00:59:05,658
and call again.

1156
00:59:05,658 --> 00:59:08,569
Did he change his number
just to avoid me?

1157
00:59:11,098 --> 00:59:13,569
How could he do that?

1158
00:59:20,709 --> 00:59:22,178
How could you...

1159
00:59:22,678 --> 00:59:23,719
Hey.

1160
00:59:23,719 --> 00:59:25,248
We should talk.

1161
00:59:25,578 --> 00:59:26,649
Hey!

1162
00:59:28,419 --> 00:59:31,189
You darn punk, stop right there!

1163
00:59:32,219 --> 00:59:33,288
Darn.

1164
00:59:34,259 --> 00:59:35,259
Gosh.

1165
00:59:40,698 --> 00:59:42,428
This is humiliating.

1166
00:59:46,399 --> 00:59:49,339
This is driving me nuts.

1167
00:59:54,709 --> 00:59:55,748
What...

1168
01:00:07,888 --> 01:00:10,359
Sure. Let's talk.

1169
01:00:13,799 --> 01:00:15,799
You keep calling it a mistake,

1170
01:00:17,939 --> 01:00:19,469
but it wasn't for me.

1171
01:00:20,868 --> 01:00:23,408
It was short and lasted one night,

1172
01:00:24,739 --> 01:00:26,709
but I let you in my heart.

1173
01:00:28,178 --> 01:00:29,509
I developed feelings for you.

1174
01:00:30,848 --> 01:00:33,518
Ma'am, come on.

1175
01:00:33,518 --> 01:00:36,219
Please don't be like this.
I'm begging you.

1176
01:00:36,319 --> 01:00:37,658
That night...

1177
01:00:37,658 --> 01:00:39,759
- was a drunken mistake.
- Did he call me "ma'am?"

1178
01:00:40,018 --> 01:00:41,089
Ma'am,

1179
01:00:42,259 --> 01:00:43,859
please forget about me.

1180
01:00:44,498 --> 01:00:46,399
If we bump into each other
on the street,

1181
01:00:46,399 --> 01:00:48,469
act like you don't know me
and keep walking. Please.

1182
01:00:51,899 --> 01:00:54,969
It wasn't even Ms. Ko.
He called me "ma'am."

1183
01:00:56,339 --> 01:00:57,379
Me?

1184
01:01:01,248 --> 01:01:02,808
One, two, three.

1185
01:01:03,009 --> 01:01:04,618
Cut. Okay, that was great.

1186
01:01:05,518 --> 01:01:06,819
- That's a wrap.
- Good job.

1187
01:01:06,819 --> 01:01:08,288
- Good job, everyone.
- Let's wrap this up.

1188
01:01:08,288 --> 01:01:09,989
- Good job, guys.
- Thank you.

1189
01:01:09,989 --> 01:01:12,089
Good job. You did great.

1190
01:01:12,189 --> 01:01:13,288
Right.

1191
01:01:13,828 --> 01:01:15,129
- Mr. Ko...
- Pil Seung!

1192
01:01:15,728 --> 01:01:17,029
- Ko Pil Seung.
- Right.

1193
01:01:18,098 --> 01:01:20,129
- Unbelievable.
- What will we be filming tomorrow?

1194
01:01:20,368 --> 01:01:21,629
You should stay warm.

1195
01:01:22,268 --> 01:01:23,739
Did you give her a hand warmer?

1196
01:01:23,739 --> 01:01:24,739
- I did.
- Good job today.

1197
01:01:28,408 --> 01:01:31,038
Mr. Ko, would you like
to join me for dinner today?

1198
01:01:31,339 --> 01:01:32,678
I have something to give you.

1199
01:01:42,348 --> 01:01:43,719
I feel terrible,

1200
01:01:43,989 --> 01:01:45,788
but I have important plans today.

1201
01:01:49,489 --> 01:01:50,799
What can you do, right?

1202
01:01:51,359 --> 01:01:52,658
There are other days.

1203
01:01:54,129 --> 01:01:55,228
I'll give it to him tomorrow.

1204
01:01:59,399 --> 01:02:00,408
Gosh.

1205
01:02:01,538 --> 01:02:04,279
Jae Dong, let's get some sushi.

1206
01:02:05,509 --> 01:02:08,379
- Sounds good.
- Let's get some sushi.

1207
01:02:08,379 --> 01:02:09,709
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

1208
01:02:13,478 --> 01:02:16,848
Seriously.
If it hadn't been for you,

1209
01:02:16,848 --> 01:02:19,319
I would've already
dropped out of this series.

1210
01:02:19,558 --> 01:02:22,428
You take my side on set,

1211
01:02:22,428 --> 01:02:25,158
join me for drinks after work,

1212
01:02:25,158 --> 01:02:26,728
and listen to me rant.

1213
01:02:26,728 --> 01:02:28,498
That's what keeps me going.

1214
01:02:31,098 --> 01:02:32,098
I mean it.

1215
01:02:32,799 --> 01:02:34,339
During the 15 years of my career,

1216
01:02:34,339 --> 01:02:36,038
there hasn't been a project
that was this hard.

1217
01:02:36,038 --> 01:02:38,739
Yesterday, you saw Snark Do Ra
throw water at my face.

1218
01:02:39,078 --> 01:02:41,149
She didn't spray the water.
She slapped me with it.

1219
01:02:41,149 --> 01:02:43,408
How can water hurt that much?

1220
01:02:43,748 --> 01:02:45,978
She must've thrown it with anger...

1221
01:02:45,978 --> 01:02:48,118
for it to have felt like
being slapped.

1222
01:02:48,118 --> 01:02:51,058
Tell me about it.
She was a bit harsh.

1223
01:02:51,158 --> 01:02:52,558
Even your skin turned red.

1224
01:02:52,558 --> 01:02:53,859
Exactly!

1225
01:02:54,029 --> 01:02:55,828
Even now, I hate looking at water...

1226
01:02:55,828 --> 01:02:59,399
because it reminds me
of her slapping me with it.

1227
01:03:03,169 --> 01:03:04,399
Because of Snark Do Ra,

1228
01:03:05,368 --> 01:03:07,868
I broke my beloved Bi Bi's heart.

1229
01:03:08,709 --> 01:03:10,509
But I have to play out
romantic scenes...

1230
01:03:10,509 --> 01:03:11,939
with all this anger
brewing inside me.

1231
01:03:12,239 --> 01:03:15,448
I mean... I... Truly...

1232
01:03:15,948 --> 01:03:17,719
Pil Seung, this is killing me.

1233
01:03:17,919 --> 01:03:19,919
Gosh. Of course
it's taking a toll on you.

1234
01:03:20,049 --> 01:03:21,919
I get how you feel.

1235
01:03:23,888 --> 01:03:25,158
That being said...

1236
01:03:26,319 --> 01:03:28,788
Tomorrow, we're filming a scene
where she slaps me while I'm kneeling.

1237
01:03:29,928 --> 01:03:31,129
I don't think I can do it.

1238
01:03:31,759 --> 01:03:34,669
Snark Do Ra might slap me
until my neck snaps.

1239
01:03:35,598 --> 01:03:38,939
Could you perhaps ask the writer...

1240
01:03:39,439 --> 01:03:41,839
to change the script?

1241
01:03:44,439 --> 01:03:45,538
I'm afraid I can't.

1242
01:03:47,478 --> 01:03:49,609
Bong Soo.

1243
01:03:50,978 --> 01:03:53,118
Snark Do Ra is making
my life miserable as well.

1244
01:03:53,448 --> 01:03:56,089
Right, of course.
It can't be easy for you either.

1245
01:03:59,558 --> 01:04:00,589
You.

1246
01:04:01,359 --> 01:04:03,489
Didn't you buy her
ice cream, tteokbokki,

1247
01:04:04,328 --> 01:04:05,799
and even flowers?

1248
01:04:07,728 --> 01:04:08,768
Are you playing...

1249
01:04:09,629 --> 01:04:10,669
both sides?

1250
01:04:12,698 --> 01:04:14,669
Bong Soo, come on.

1251
01:04:15,509 --> 01:04:17,379
I didn't do it because I wanted to.

1252
01:04:17,879 --> 01:04:19,538
It was to make your life easier.

1253
01:04:19,678 --> 01:04:22,379
Catering to her every whim
will make things easier for you.

1254
01:04:22,379 --> 01:04:23,779
That's why I'm doing it.

1255
01:04:24,178 --> 01:04:26,819
But putting up with her
isn't a stroll in the park.

1256
01:04:26,819 --> 01:04:29,089
I now get
why people call her Snark Do Ra.

1257
01:04:29,089 --> 01:04:31,558
I lose my mind
dozens of times a day!

1258
01:04:49,359 --> 01:04:52,129
(Beauty and Mr. Romantic)

1259
01:05:24,429 --> 01:05:26,790
I sent a food truck
to support you on set,

1260
01:05:26,790 --> 01:05:28,230
but I thought I should
support you in person too.

1261
01:05:28,230 --> 01:05:30,259
Mr. Gong, how sweet of you.

1262
01:05:30,259 --> 01:05:32,199
I feel bad to always be
on the receiving end.

1263
01:05:32,199 --> 01:05:33,629
Treat me to a meal next time, then.

1264
01:05:33,770 --> 01:05:35,299
Stay out of my sight.

1265
01:05:35,299 --> 01:05:36,739
If I ever catch a glimpse of you,

1266
01:05:37,040 --> 01:05:39,910
I'll kill you!

1267
01:05:39,910 --> 01:05:41,279
What is it that I just saw?

1268
01:05:41,279 --> 01:05:42,839
Just wait till your mom finds out...

1269
01:05:42,839 --> 01:05:44,210
how you've been
letting her treat you.

1270
01:05:44,210 --> 01:05:46,009
Your mom will faint from the shock.

1271
01:05:46,009 --> 01:05:47,250
It's never the work that's hard.

1272
01:05:47,480 --> 01:05:48,580
It's the people around me.

1273
01:05:48,920 --> 01:05:50,319
Has someone been making
your life miserable?

1274
01:05:50,319 --> 01:05:51,489
Who is it?

1275
01:05:51,489 --> 01:05:52,790
I'll knock some sense
into whoever that is.

1276
01:05:52,790 --> 01:05:55,190
From this day forward,
we'll never see each other again.

1277
01:05:55,942 --> 01:05:58,052
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
